column5: Photo posted by Chris Hadfield on twitter today.   Barrie 12:40pm
Don't suppose you could shoot him and e-mail and get him to aim a little more to the right, eh?  Save driving all the way around to Port B.
His brother lives out your way too. He posted photos of TO, Ottawa, Kingston and Montreal. Maybe you're out the other window?
How about get in your car and go see for yourself? What ever happened to those days?  S.
Those days I could fill my car for 50 cents a litre.
And there was no internet.......and lots of fish.......and hardly any fisherman.......I miss those days!

Well matter of fact I did this morning, left home at 09:10 one quick stop for a java to go and got to Virginia Beach around 10:30.  Over to Port Bolster, Caseys for a quick chat along the lake rd for a bit and then back home for 2:20. Found a few of the small parking spots that get gobbled up pretty quick on weekends.
They are long gone, just like common sense and politeness.
Whats Virginia Beach looking like? I'd drive over and check it out but its about 2 hours from me
from what I see on the photo it's frozen to the island but the ferry is still going
Atta boy. I've done that drive a few times myself. It was a nice day for a look see today.  S.
Not great, I'd give it another 3-4 duyas just to be safe.
